goals.question: What is the average yield of barley across all sites and years?
goals.rationale: A box plot can show the median, quartiles, and outliers of the yield distribution, giving an idea of the central tendency and spread of the data.

goals.question: How does the yield vary across different barley varieties?
goals.visualization: violin plot of yield by variety
goals.rationale: A violin plot can show the distribution of yield for each variety, allowing for comparison of the central tendency and spread of the data across different categories.

goals.question: What is the trend in yield over time?
goals.visualization: line plot of yield by year
goals.rationale: A line plot can show the trend in yield over time, allowing for identification of any patterns or changes in the data.

goals.question: How does the yield vary across different sites?
goals.visualization: bar chart of mean yield by site
goals.rationale: A bar chart can show the mean yield for each site, allowing for comparison of the central tendency of the data across different locations.

goals.question: Is there a relationship between yield and variety?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of yield by variety
goals.rationale: A scatter plot can show the relationship between yield and variety, allowing for identification of any patterns or correlations in the data.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.boxplot(x='year', y='yield', data=data)
    median_yield = data['yield'].median()
    plt.axhline(y=median_yield, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Median Yield: {median_yield:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the average yield of barley across all sites and years?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.violinplot(x='variety', y='yield', data=data)
    plt.title('How does the yield vary across different barley varieties?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Variety')
    plt.ylabel('Yield (bushels per acre)')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
